    "body": "The new string compression is great for modules with large number or long strings, but not all modules fall in that category. Moreover, decompression depends on stdlib modules that may not be available if Python is specially configured/built. This forces users to define `CYTHON_COMPRESS_STRING=0`, and how to do that depends on the details of the build system (setuptools, cmake, meson, etc). It would be great to allow module authors to turn off the string compression feature via compiler directive.\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-28T07:20:33Z",
